properties.headline: Wind Chill Warning issued February 12 at 6:03PM CST until February 13 at 9:00AM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...DANGEROUS WIND CHILLS THROUGH MID MORNING THURSDAY...

.Temperatures will continue to drop off sharply behind the
arctic front this evening. Wind chill values are dropping to 40
to 50 degrees below zero over west central Minnesota this evening,
with wind chills of 30 to 40 degrees below zero expected across
eastern Minnesota and western Wisconsin overnight. These dangerous
wind chills will continue into mid-morning Thursday.

In addition, some blowing snow will continue through late evening
across western and southern Minnesota where a Winter Weather
Advisory has replaced the Blizzard Warning.

* WHAT...For the Wind Chill Warning, dangerously cold wind
chills expected. Wind chills as low as 40 below zero. For the
Winter Weather Advisory, blowing snow. Winds gusting as high
as 35 mph.

* WHERE...Waseca, Steele and Freeborn Counties.

* WHEN...For the Wind Chill Warning, from 9 PM this evening to 9
AM CST Thursday. For the Winter Weather Advisory, until 10 PM
CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Patchy blowing snow could significantly reduce
visibility. The hazardous conditions could impact the morning
commute. The dangerously cold wind chills could cause
frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Avoid outside activities if possible. When outside, make sure you
wear appropriate clothing, a hat, and gloves.

Use caution while traveling, especially in open areas.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
